<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 2:56AM CDT  by NWS Austin-San Antonio</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Uvalde and
northeastern Zavala Counties through 330 AM CDT...
At 256 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Blewett, or 14 miles west of Uvalde, moving east at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Uvalde, Uvalde Estates, Blewett and Cline.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 300 AM CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
